

====================: STEP: 01 :=====================



ROUTER-01: HEAD_OFFICE
-------------------
WAN: 192.168.70.2/30
DNS: 8.8.8.8,8.8.4.4
GATEWAY: 192.168.70.1
LAN: 10.10.11.1/24

interface ethernet set name=ISP [ find default-name=ether1 ]
interface ethernet set name=LAN [ find default-name=ether2 ]                    
ip address add address=192.168.70.2/30 interface=ISP                        
ip address add address=10.10.11.1/24 interface=LAN                              
ip dns set servers=8.8.8.8,8.8.4.4 allow-remote-requests=yes cache-size=10000
ip route add gateway=192.168.70.1
ip dhcp-server setup
                                          
ip firewall nat add chain=srcnat out-interface=ISP action=masquerade 

--------------------

ROUTER-02: BRANCH
---------------
WAN: 192.168.80.2/30
DNS: 8.8.8.8,8.8.4.4
GATEWAY: 192.168.80.1
LAN: 10.10.12.1/24

interface ethernet set name=ISP [ find default-name=ether1 ]
interface ethernet set name=LAN [ find default-name=ether2 ]                    
ip address add address=192.168.80.2/30 interface=ISP                        
ip address add address=10.10.12.1/24 interface=LAN                              
ip dns set servers=8.8.8.8,8.8.4.4 allow-remote-requests=yes cache-size=10000
ip route add gateway=192.168.80.1
ip dhcp-server setup
                                          
ip firewall nat add chain=srcnat out-interface=ISP action=masquerade    


=====================: STEP: 02 :=======================

IPsec Peer Configuration in Router 01:
--------------------------------------
ip ipsec peer add name=NAME-A-PEER address=REMOTE-ROUTER-IP port=500
ip ipsec identity  add peer=peer01 secret=123


IPsec Peer Configuration in Router 02:
--------------------------------------
ip ipsec peer add name=NAME-A-PEER address=REMOTE-ROUTER-IP port=500
ip ipsec identity  add peer=peer01 secret=123

====================: STEP: 03 :======================

NAT Bypass Rule Configuration in Router 01:
===========================================
ip firewall nat add chain=srcnat src-address=10.10.11.1/24(LOCAL-LAN-IP) dst-address=10.10.12.1/24(DEST-LAN-IP) action=accept


NAT Bypass Rule Configuration in Router 02:
===========================================
ip firewall nat add chain=srcnat src-address=10.10.12.1/24(LOCAL-LAN-IP) dst-address=10.10.11.1/24(DEST-LAN-IP) action=accept





